      • addNode

        public static void addNode(INode root)
        This method acts as a menu option. When selected it will add a child node to a parent of the user's choice. If the parent doesn't exist or has two children, an error will be displayed.
        Parameters:
        root - The root of the binary tree add a node to.

      • findNode

        public static void findNode(INode root)
        This method acts as a menu option. When selected it will find if a node exists with a character the user enters.
        Parameters:
        root - The root of the binary tree to find the node in.

      • getTreeSize

        public static void getTreeSize(INode root)
        This method acts as a menu option. When selected it will retrieve the size of a binary tree with a root the user enters.
        Parameters:
        root - The root of the binary tree to get the size of.

      • promptForCharacter

        public static java.lang.String promptForCharacter()
        Propmts the user to enter a character. If the input is invalid, the user is forced to enter a valid character. Otherwise, the character is returned.
        Returns:
        The character the user entered.

      • promptForMenuOption

        public static int promptForMenuOption()
        Prompts the user to select a menu option. If it fails, it tells the user that their input was invalid, and returns -1. Otherwise, it returns the value the user entered.
        Returns:
        The menu option the user selected.
